records.addlTxt:
Defendant Samuel A Sorensen in court with attorney Jason David Luczak.  Joshua Miles Mathy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Court reviewed the video of the incidents. Court ordered the disc be marked as Exhibit 1 and received into the record. State placed negotiations on the record. Statements made as to sentencing. 

AS to COUNT 1 AMENDED and COUNT 2 AMENDED-
The Court WITHHELD sentence and placed defendant on probation for a period of 12 months with the following conditions:
If revoked, Court ordered COUNTS 1 AMENDED and 2 AMENDED be concurrent to one another.

1) Defendant is to be supervised by the mental health unit;
2) Continue counseling with Dr. Jensen at Shorehaven as deemed appropriate by provider;
3) Continue treatment with Dr. Batory at American Behavioral Clinics;
4) No contact with the victim or his family or residence;
5) No violent contact with James H.;
6) Pay restitution in the amount of $221.89 to be paid to Nicole D. Restitution to be paid first before costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
7) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
8) Remain enrolled in school full time;
9) Write a letter of apology to the victim's family and provide the letter to the agent. Counsel to provide a copy of the letter the Court at the probation review date;
10) Court did not order a DNA sample or a DNA surcharge because it is not mandatory in this matter;

Court ordered a progress report be prepared for the probation review date. 

Court will defer ruling on expunction until the review date. Court will retain this case post-rotation. Exhibit List received and filed. Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed. Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for April 14, 2016 at 08:30 am.
